The paper deals with the security of data transmission over wireless networks, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the implications of cooperation and power allocation, which are relevant to the fields of cryptography and network security (cs.CR). The use of wireless networks and the analysis of different cooperative scenarios suggest that the paper could also be classified under the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a distributed algorithm for device selection and power allocation, which could be relevant to the field of multimedia (cs.MM) in terms of optimizing data transmission rates.
